.nh
.TH "BCDOCK" "1" "Jan 2025" "BCDock CLI" "BCDock Manual"

.SH NAME
bcdock-auth-signup - Activate your BCDock account using an invite code


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbcdock auth signup [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Activate your account after receiving an invite code via email.

.PP
If you don't have an invite code yet, join the waitlist first:
  bcdock auth join-waitlist

.PP
Once you have a code, run:
  bcdock auth signup --invite-code ABCD1234 --email you@example.com

.PP
The CLI looks up your waitlist entry via the invite code and pre-fills any
BC config you supplied at waitlist time. After activation, run:
  bcdock auth login --email you@example.com

.PP
to receive an OTP and complete login. The first BC environment is queued
automatically when activation succeeds (if a complete config is available).

.PP
Exit codes:
  0   ok
  1   general error (invalid invite code, email mismatch)
  4   rate-limited


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--accept-eula\fP[=false]
	Accept the Microsoft NAV/BC on Docker EULA

.PP
\fB--accept-insider-eula\fP[=false]
	Accept the BC Insider EULA (preview versions)

.PP
\fB--artifact-type\fP=""
	Artifact type: Sandbox or OnPrem

.PP
\fB--bc-version\fP=""
	BC version (e.g. 27.5)

.PP
\fB--country\fP=""
	BC country code (e.g. AU)

.PP
\fB--email\fP=""
	Email address (the one your invite was issued for)

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for signup

.PP
\fB--invite-code\fP=""
	Invite code from your waitlist invite email

.PP
\fB--multi-tenant\fP=""
	true|false - multi-tenant container

.PP
\fB--name\fP=""
	Display name (defaults to waitlist entry name if any)

.PP
\fB--region\fP=""
	Azure region (e.g. australiaeast)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--api-url\fP=""
	API base URL (env: BCDOCK_API_URL)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colored output

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP="table"
	Output format: table, json, csv

.PP
\fB-q\fP, \fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	Suppress non-essential output

.PP
\fB--timeout\fP=30s
	Request timeout

.PP
\fB--token\fP=""
	API token (env: BCDOCK_TOKEN)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  bcdock auth signup --invite-code ABCD1234 --email you@example.com
  bcdock auth signup --invite-code ABCD1234 --email you@example.com --bc-version 25.5 --country au
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBbcdock-auth(1)\fP
